{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HiusThPSPbk7rqHAGZ4Jp4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I could add a `drift` kernel that just applies `pos += vel * dt` without running the full grid + flock pipeline. On odd frames, just run drift. On even frames, run the full pipeline.\n\nBut this requires a new shader entry point. Let me add a simple `drift` kernel to the shader.\n\nActually, wait. The simpler approach: on odd frames, skip the grid rebuild and flock, and just let the position be stale (since the render reads the current buffer directly). But that would mean boids don't move on odd frames, which is visually obvious.\n \nSo the better approach is to add a `drift` kernel that just updates positions based on velocity without any flocking or grid calculations, then alternate between running the full pipeline on even frames and just the drift kernel on odd frames. This should give me the performance boost I'm looking for.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1808,"cache_read_input_tokens":136819,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1808},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9036d8f4-067e-45b6-b2b3-1c0500e3d4cd","uuid":"e15b5725-f48b-4426-acef-29f504d1da2d"}
